agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Under the Freedom of Information Act, I am requesting access to the following documents: 1. All documents concerning the Listeria monocytogenes outbreak described above, including but not limited to, informal and formal findings, notes, memos, e-mails, faxes, interviews, patient questionnaires, digital recordings, audio and videotapes, and documents reviewed, both internal to your agency and interagency; 2. All documents establishing a chain of custody for any cultures, isolates, or samples obtained or analyzed by any agency involved in investigating the outbreak; 3. Lab notebooks, records, and worksheets regarding the outbreak; 4. Electronic images/genetic or DNA fingerprinting/.tif files regarding the outbreak; 5. All isolates/bacterial strains obtained from any patient, food sample, animal, manure, or the environment that is believed to be related to or associated with the outbreak; 6. All isolates/bacterial strains obtained from any food product that is believed to be related to or associated with the outbreak; 7. All documents that relate to, comment on, or discuss any agency’s effort to trace the strain or strains of Listeria monocytogenes causing the outbreak to any source; 8. All communication (including e-mails) and notes regarding communications between CDC food safety officials and the FDA, USDA-FSIS, and any other city, county, state, or other public health agency (including public health laboratories), regarding the above-referenced 2021 Listeria monocytogenes outbreak linked to Dole packaged salads; 9. All data maintained on the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention PulseNet database concerning any patients infected during the outbreak; 10. The PulseNet Cluster Code (Outbreak Code) assigned to this outbreak; 11. All data maintained on the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention PulseNet database regarding any strain obtained from any animal, manure, or the environment that is believed, based upon genetic or DNA fingerprinting, to be related to or a match to the strain causing the outbreak; 12. Any other additional information or records regarding the outbreak. (Date Range for Record Search: From 1/1/2014 To 1/3/2022)

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: request for all studies and/or reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and/or the Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR) describing the purification (i.e. via filtration, ultracentrifugation and chromatography) of any "Marburg virus", directly from a sample taken from a diseased human or non-human primate, where the sample was not first combined with any other source of genetic material (i.e. a cell line; fetal bovine serum). Please note that I am not requesting studies/reports where researchers failed to purify the suspected "virus" and instead: • cultured something, and/or • performed an amplification test (i.e. PCR), and/or • fabricated a "genome", and/or • produced electron microscopy images of unpurified things. For further clarity, please note I am already aware that according to virus theory a "virus" requires host cells in order to replicate, and I am not requesting records describing the replication of a "virus" without host cells.

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Upon the direction of BP America Production Company and/or BP Exploration and Production (“BP”), National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH) investigators completed exposure monitoring, observational assessments, health surveys, and focus groups for a variety of work sites and work activities related to the Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill (DHOS). Per NIOSH Interim Report 4, attached as Exhibit A, the Health Hazard Evaluation (HHE) conducted Personal Breathing Zone (PBZ) air sampling for benzene and other Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs) using passive Organic Vapor Monitors (OVMs) and charcoal tubes that were submitted for laboratory analyses. Charcoal OVM badges were placed on personnel identified as having the highest potential for exposure and charcoal tubes also were used to determine airborne concentrations of contaminants. The NIOSH HHE study findings were released in a series of nine interim reports as well as a final report published August 2011, attached as Exhibit B. The NIOSH DHOS HHE mostly reported that contaminants were below Occupational Exposure Limits (OEL) or not detected in air monitoring and PBZ assessments. This includes onshore and offshore airborne contaminants for VOCs and Polycyclic Aromatic Hydrocarbons (PAHs) as well as monitoring of chemicals of concern in COREXIT dispersants. In addition, dermal exposure risks were calculated primarily through observational methods. Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. § 552, The Downs Law Group (DLG) requests any and all records from April 20, 2010, to present, archived by NIOSH or the CDC regarding the following information and/or documents that are articulated in the "Description Document" attachment. (Date Range for Record Search: From 04/20/2010 To 12/31/2021)

request_text: All studies and/or reports in the possession, custody or control of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) describing the purification of the alleged “COVID-19 virus” (aka “SARS-COV-2”, including any alleged “variants”) directly from a sample taken from a diseased human, where the patient sample was not first combined with any other source of genetic material (i.e. monkey kidney cells aka Vero cells; fetal bovine serum). Clarification of Request: Please note that I am not requesting studies/reports where researchers failed to purify the suspected “virus” and instead: cultured something, and/or performed an amplification test (i.e. PCR), and/or fabricated a genome from sequences (allegedly) detected in an impure substance, and/or produced electron microscopy images of unpurified things. I am already aware that according to virus theory a “virus” requires host cells in order to replicate, and am not requesting records that describe replication of a ‘virus’ without host cells. Nor am I requesting records that describe a strict fulfillment of Koch’s Postulates, or records that describe a suspected “virus” floating in a vacuum, or private patient information. I simply request records that describe purification (separation of the alleged virus from everything else in the patient sample, as per standard laboratory practices for the purification of other very small things). Please note that my request includes any study/report matching the above description, authored by anyone, anywhere. If any records match the above description of requested records and are currently available in the public domain, please provide enough information about each record so that I may identify and access each one with certainty (i.e. title, author(s), date, journal, where the public may access it). Please provide URLs where possible. Format: Pdf documents sent to me via email; I do not wish for anything to be shipped to me

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Summary of request: Proof that un-regulated masks, as ordered by the CDC on US Citizens, stop Covid containing aerosols. By proof we mean scientific, not social. It must indisputable, reproducible, experimentally verifiable proof that un-regulated masks, as mandated by the CDC from the beginning of the pandemic, can stop even one single Covid containing aerosol. Definition of aerosol for this request: The definition of aerosol can be confusing, so we use the word the way NASA and other engineering / science organizations use it. An aerosols is a super-tiny droplet, so small that it floats even though it is pure liquid. This must be distinguished from droplets in general which can vary in size. All aerosols are droplets, but all droplets are not aerosols. Most doctors use the words aerosol and droplet interchangeably. They are not interchangeable in Science. Covid does not usually cause coughing or sneezing, and is transmitted via exhalation and aerosols, not ballistic droplets.

request_text: Recently, U.S. Representatives on the House Oversight and Judiciary committee released excerpts of emails that they say reveal National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Disease Director Dr. Anthony Fauci knew early on that COVID-19 may have leaked from the Wuhan Institute of Virology.i These congressmen said that “it is unclear if either Dr. Fauci or Dr. Collins (former National Institutes of Health Director) ever passed these warnings along to other government officials or if they simply ignored them.” It is imperative that this be investigated. We are seeking all records that contain communications with the public, members of the media, state and local government officials, or members of Congress and/or their staff about this issue. We understand some information may be redacted and all redactions will be properly cited. It also includes records documenting or discussing public relations strategies concerning this issue, as well as communications discussing this issue. Specifically, we request that a search include the Office of the Secretary (including the White House Liaison), Office of Public Affairs, Office of Legislative Affairs, and other related offices that may contain relevant records. 2. External communications pertaining to the COVID-19 Lab Leak Theory: All records that pertain to the COVID-19 Lab Leak Theory within and between the HHS offices listed above and the White House, State Department, Department of Defense, Department of Homeland Security, and other relevant federal officials.

request_text: I would like to obtain a listing of site locations that are, known to be or suspected to be, contaminated with PFAS chemicals, for the entire United States, in spreadsheet format. PFAS is a class of chemicals that includes PFOA (perfluorooctanoic acid), PFOS (perfluorooctanesulfonic acid), PFNA (perfluorononanoic acid) and PFHxA (perfluorohexanoic acid). PFOA and PFOS, are the most commonly found and potent PFASs at contamination sites. ATSDR is involved at a number of PFAS-related sites, either directly or through assisting state and federal partners. As of now, most sites are related to drinking water contamination connected with PFAS production facilities or fire training areas where aqueous film-forming firefighting foam (AFFF) was regularly used. We are working with one state partner on a site where consuming contaminated fish is the concern. Information I would like includes: Region contact information: Contact name Contact title Contact phone number Contact fax number Contact email address Site information: Site name Site location address Site location city Site location state Site location zip code Latitude Longitude Detail information Contaminant information: PFAS substance Source of contamination Media affected

agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Since the 1970s, CDC has administered a Vessel Sanitation Program (“VSP”) in cooperation with cruise ships, and under the authority of the Public Health Service Act (42 U.S.C. Section 264). Every cruise vessel that has a foreign itinerary, carries 13 or more passengers, and calls on a U.S. port is subject to biannual unannounced operational inspections and, when necessary, reinspection by VSP. Additionally, cruise vessel owners or shipyards that build or renovate cruise vessels may voluntarily request plan reviews, onsite shipyard construction inspections, and/or final construction inspections of new or renovated vessels before their first or next operational inspection. I request that a copy of the following documents (or documents containing the following information) generated as part of the VSP program be provided to me: 1. Any audits, inspection reports, or reinspection reports generated during the years 1986-1990 for the HOMERIC (re-named WESTERDAM in 1988) or the ATLANTIC (re-named STARSHIP ATLANTIC in 1988), whether the inspection was for sanitation purposes or construction purposes. During those years, the owner/operator of these vessels would have been one of the following: a. Home Lines Inc., Home Lines Cruises, Inc. (or any Home Lines entity); b. a Holland America Line entity; c. a Carnival Corporation entity; d. Premier Cruise Line e. Merchant Ships Trustees Ltd. 2. request_text: Please see the attached letter for details for this request regarding cloth masks. FGI requests from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) all records from January 1, 2020, to the date CDC conducts the search meeting the following criteria: 1. Any analysis or similar type of document discussing how a cloth mask would protect against COVID-19. This should include health, legal, economic, regulatory, or other analysis or peer-reviewed studies prepared by or sent to the CDC officials identified below. 2. Any calendar items, emails with attachments, meeting memos, briefing documents, presentations for meetings, and other records discussing or pertaining to the analyses under the previous paragraph and received by or sent by the CDC officials and staff identified below. We can provide some search terms to facilitate the search: • “Efficacy of cloth masks” • “Effectiveness of cloth masks” • “Cloth masks and COVID-19” • “Coronavirus and cloth masks” • “Cloth face coverings” • “Study of” any of the terms above • “Analysis of” any of the terms above • “Review of” any of the terms above • “Effective tool” in combination with any of the terms above • “Double masking” • Any formal report or analysis that includes “cloth masks” in its title For the above criteria, please include search for records held by the personnel listed below, including anyone who may have left the agency but formerly worked in positions during the time range of this request. • The Director, • The Principal Deputy Director, • The Deputy Director for Infectious Diseases, • The Deputy Director for Public Health Service and Implementation Science, • The Deputy Director for Public Health Science and Surveillance, and • CDC Washington Office Director. The term “all records” in this request refers to, but is not limited to all documents, letters, correspondence, emails including attachments, schedules and calendar entries, electronic meeting invitations and replies, facsimiles, memoranda, text messages, notes from meetings and telephone calls, minutes of meetings, agendas of meetings, comments, files, presentations, consultations, drawings, diagrams, graphs, charts, assessments, evaluations, telephone records and logs, virtual meeting logs such as those produced by Microsoft Teams, papers (published or unpublished), reports, studies, photographs and other images, databases, data, maps, and/or all other responsive records in draft or final form that fall within the definition of “agency records” subject to FOIA. agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: Please see the attached letter for details on this request related to random control tests. FGI requests from the CDC all records from March 1, 2020, to the date CDC conducts the search meeting the following criteria: 1. Internal communications: All meeting requests, emails with attachments, meeting memos, briefing documents, schedules, and any other records created, received, or otherwise in the possession of any employee in offices listed below discussing “randomized controlled trials” or “RCTs” as it pertains to the public’s use of masks (any type of mask) to protect against COVID-19. 2. All records of communications that discuss the following: a. whether to fund RCTs to study mask efficacy in preventing or reducing the spread of COVID-19, b. evaluating any proposals for RCTs to study the efficacy of masks to protect against COVID-19, or c. response to articles or public commentary on the need for RCTs to study mask efficacy. 3. External communications: all communications, documents, and other records to, from, or between any person in the offices listed below and any non-governmental organization, lobbyist, or corporation discussing RCTs as they pertain to the efficacy of masks to protect against COVID-19. 4. Communications with Congress: all communications, documents, and other records to, from, or between any person in the offices listed below and any employee of the legislative branch, including a committee staff member, Congressional office aide, or Congressional Member, pertaining to RCTs studying the efficacy of masks to protect against COVID-19. For reference, email addresses for these persons typically end with house.gov or senate.gov. 5. Any analysis discussing why RCTs studying the efficacy of masks to protect against COVID-19 have not been funded. This should include health, legal, economic, regulatory, or other analysis prepared by or provided to any person in the offices listed below. Please note that for the criteria above, “randomized controlled trials” and “RCTs” are used interchangeably, so when searching, both terms should be used. Also, it could be spelled as “randomised" with an “s” instead of a “z” in some cases. 6. There are additional search suggestions in the letter. For the above criteria, please include search for records held by the offices listed below, including anyone who left the agency and formerly worked in these positions during the time range of this request. • The Director, • The Principal Deputy Director, • The Deputy Director for Infectious Diseases, • The Deputy Director for Public Health Service and Implementation Science, • The Deputy Director for Public Health Science and Surveillance, and • CDC Washington Office Director. The term “all records” in this request refers to a detailed list in the attached letter. Thank you. (Date Range for Record Search: From 03/01/2020 To 03/15/2022)

request_text: Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records: 1. Copies of all data, reports, presentations, records, agendas, and meeting minutes related to COVID-19 vaccines and pregnancy and/or pregnant people as part of the CDC's v-safe COVID-19 Vaccine Pregnancy Registry that were presented to, or included in, meetings of the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices (ACIP), including but not limited to all relevant data collected and/or reported by Abt Associates (https://www.abtassociates.com/projects/expanding-v-safe-covid-19-vaccine-pregnancy-registry-0) between Dec. 1, 2020 and the date this request is ultimately processed. 2. agency_name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
request_text: This request pertains to the number of COVID-19 post-vaccination deaths (currently at 12,775) published on the CDC's website (https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/vaccines/safety/adverse-events.html) in the bulleted section "Reports of death after COVID-19 vaccination are rare"._x000B_Specifically, I would like to know: 1. Does the number displayed reflect the TOTAL number of post-vaccination deaths recorded in VAERS for the specified date range…or only a subset of the total? 2. What criteria constitutes a post-vaccination death? Is it simply that the patient died at some point after being vaccinated…or are there other conditions to consider? 3. What criteria is currently used to calculate post-vaccination deaths published on the website? 4. Which fields from the VAERS data is used in the current calculation? 5. VAERS database appears to record deaths in more than one field. Who made the decision as to which field(s) to use for calculating the published deaths and what was the reason(s) behind it? 6. Has the calculation or data fields used in the calculation for the published post-vaccination deaths ever changed over time, and if so, for all instances: a. When was it done? b. Exactly what was changed in the calculation? c. Who authorized it? d. What was reason for the change? This request stems from the fact that some 3rd-party websites which claim to use the VAERS data are reporting 24,827 total deaths post-vaccination. After querying the VAERS data myself, I can see that the 12K figure is based on the patient having a Symptom of 'death', while the 24K figure is based on the patient having an Event of 'death'. Furthermore, the dataset for the 24K figure has the Date of Death populated...so surely that must be the correct figure, and the CDC is under-reporting?? (Date Range for Record Search: From 01/01/2019 To 03/11/2022)
